sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant PyPI as PyPI<br/>pypi.org<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines API<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Tekton as Tekton/Argo<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Notebook
    User->>Router: GET /<br/>OAuth2 session cookie
    Router->>OAuth: HTTPS/8443<br/>OAuth2 token validation
    OAuth->>Jupyter: HTTP/8888 (localhost)<br/>Trusted (same pod)
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: Jupyter UI HTML
    OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>User: Jupyter Interface<br/>TLS 1.2+ encrypted

    Note over Jupyter,PyPI: Flow 2: Notebook Installs Python Package
    Jupyter->>PyPI: pip install pandas<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>No auth
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package wheel file<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over Jupyter,S3: Flow 3: Notebook Accesses S3 Data
    Jupyter->>S3: GET s3://bucket/dataset.csv<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+<br/>AWS IAM credentials (from secret)
    S3-->>Jupyter: CSV data<br/>AWS signature validation

    Note over Jupyter,Tekton: Flow 4: Elyra Submits Pipeline
    Jupyter->>KFP: POST /apis/v1beta1/pipelines<br/>HTTP/8888<br/>K8s ServiceAccount token
    KFP->>Jupyter: Pipeline ID<br/>Token validation
    KFP->>Tekton: Create PipelineRun<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>Internal cluster auth
    Tekton-->>KFP: Pipeline execution started

    Note over User: Flow 5: CodeServer/RStudio Health Check
    rect rgb(240, 240, 240)
        Note over OAuth,Jupyter: Kubelet → NGINX (8888) → code-server/rstudio (8787)<br/>All HTTP localhost, no auth
    end
